race.comment: SEE YA LATER BABY (2) is yet to strike through this campaign when sent out favourite in all in three starts but has missed by less than a head in two of them. Peaking now and can get the job done this time in a thinner contest. CROWN AND ANCHOR (8) chased gamely into the placings at big odds when resuming at Clare. Nowhere near as good last time but has been kept on the fresh side for this and can get things back on track. MUFFLA (12) battled on soundly into a midfield finish when resuming off a long break at Naracoorte 12 days ago. Better for the run and should blend into the race nicely from the middle draw. IN THAT MODE (1) is drawn poorly but is a likely improver that can be kept safe.
